i wasn't in the market for a watch, but at its price i had to try it  basically, an app on your phone sends notifications to the watch, which can beep or vibrate  their app lets you select which apps push to the watch, and adds sms and call service  i'm on version 1 1 43 now  
 
the display is good enough for reading texts and emails, and okay at rendering pictures and video  if your phone is unlocked, the watch can start a remote capture from your phone's camera  
 
i keep my phone on silent, and the watch on vibrate  when i get a notification, i check the watch  i like being able to view or change a song without pulling out my phone  the battery life is about a work day  
 
the only complaints i have are about the dated tech  the mic, speaker, and camera seem flip phone era  the touchscreen does the job  the vibration is on the verge of being a distress signal, but does get my attention  has all the advantages of being cheap, without the loss of too much quality

 brass lead screw guide needs to be loose, or you will have too much tension on the z axis
